# Interaction Polish

- Keep interactions calm: reserve haptics for meaningful actions (save/favorite/reaction), not every tap.
- Use shared helpers (`AppHaptics`) instead of ad hoc feedback generators in views.
- Prefer subtle motion and transitions; avoid heavy or stacked animations that distract from content.
- Always provide explicit loading and error feedback with `SkeletonCard` and `ErrorStateCard`.
- Favor icon clarity and tap targets (`>=44pt`) over dense text buttons in constrained toolbars.

## Haptic Guardrail

```swift
// Good: meaningful state change
Button {
    AppHaptics.selection()
    toggleFavorite()
} label: { Image(systemName: "star") }
```
